Suggestions 5

1) A new report in CFPB Making Ends Meet survey series finds that, despite these volatile economic conditions, the average consumer’s financial status and ability to stay on top of their finances improved between June 2019 and June 2020. These results suggest that public and private interventions, such as expanded unemployment benefits and loan forbearance, alongside consumers’ own spending reductions, helped to buffer household finances during the initial months of the pandemic.

2)The Public policy interventions meaningfully supported consumers’ financial status early in the pandemic. Many of these programs will eventually end and their end will likely have a significant impact on consumers’ financial status going forward unless additional actions are taken.



https://www.usa.gov/covid-financial-help-from-the-government
